SIMPLE: linguadental
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Linguadental
<hw>Lin`gua*den"tal</hw>
<pr>(l⟦icr⟧⟦nsm⟧`gw⟦adot⟧*d⟦ecr⟧n"t⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lingua</ets> tongue + E. <ets>dental</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Phonetics)</fld> <def>Formed or uttered by the joint use of the
tongue and teeth, or rather that part of the gum just above the front
teeth; dentolingual, as the letters <xex>d</xex> and
<xex>t</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Linguadental</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Linguadental
<hw>Lin`gua*den"tal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Phonetics)</fld> <def>An
articulation pronounced by the aid or use of the tongue and
teeth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lingua Franca</ent>⟦br⟧
